<p><span class="scriptRef" com="scn" lang="eng" ref="ac+19:25">Acts 19:25</span>. <strong> Whom he called together with the workmen of like occupation. </strong> No doubt this Demetrius, who was probably chief of the ‘guild’ of silversmiths, as we should say, summoned a meeting of the various trades who derived their livelihood in one way or another from the temple of Diana and the pilgrims who resorted to her shrine.
	</p>
